<!doctype html><html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1"><title>Ed Hatrick Smith - Web: designer / developer / problem solver</title><meta name="description" content="Ed Hatrick-Smith: Southern Suzuki project"/><meta name="keywords" content="web developer, desginer, photographer, awesome person, solutions"/><meta name="author" content="Edward Hatrick-Smith: ed.hatricksmith@gmail.com"/><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/css/styles.projects.min.css"/><?php $thisPage="work";?><?php include_once("/home/akolob/public_html/analyticstracking.php") ?></head><body><?php include("/home/akolob/public_html/header.php");?><div id="projects"><h1 class="works_heading">Southern Suzuki website</h1><p class="breadcrumbs"><em><a href="/work/work.php">Work</a> / Southern Suzuki</em></p><article><p class="projects_first"><a href="http://www.southernsuzuki.co.nz/" target="_blank">Southern Suzuki</a> are one of the largest Suzuki Motorcycle dealers in New Zealand. They had recently had their site designed and built by another business and Southern Suzuki were less than impressed with the results. The site wasn't built particularly poorly but simply did not reflect their brand or appeal to their target demographic. Their brief to us was to rebuild the site but align it very closely aesthetically to Suzuki's own site.</p>
<p>Carbon now produces almost all multi-page sites using <span class="small-cap">cms</span> platforms. This makes it difficult for me to find recent examples that have been hand coded. This site is not new and only has a spatter of <span class="small-cap">hmtl5</span>, nor is it responsive, but it is still cleanly coded and a respectable example.</p></article><section><h2 class="works_heading">Project Images</h2><div id="container" class="project_width"><a class="fancybox gallery" href="/images/works/projects/southernsuzuki/image_01_lge.jpg"><div class="project project_sm"><img src="/images/works/projects/southernsuzuki/image_01_sml.jpg" alt="Southern Suzki - home page"><div class="caption fade-caption"><h3 class="element_title">Enlarge</h3></div></div></a><a class="fancybox gallery" href="/images/works/projects/southernsuzuki/image_02_lge.jpg"><div class="project project_sm"><img src="/images/works/projects/southernsuzuki/image_02_sml.jpg" alt="Southern Suzki - about page"><div class="caption fade-caption"><h3 class="element_title">Enlarge</h3></div></div></a></div><div class="clearfix"></div></section><ul><li><a href="http://www.southernsuzuki.co.nz/" target="_blank">Visit Website</a></li></ul></div><div class="clearfix"></div><?php include("/home/akolob/public_html/footer.php");?><script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.9.0/jquery.min.js"></script><script src="/js/jquery.projects.min.js" ></script><script type="text/javascript">$(".fancybox") .attr('rel', 'gallery') .fancybox({padding : 0 ,minWidth : 215 ,maxWidth : 900 ,autoSize : true ,maxHeight : 600 ,});</script><script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.9.0/jquery.min.js"></script><script src="/js/jquery.isotope-min.js"></script><script type="text/javascript">$(function(){var $container=$('#container');$container.isotope({itemSelector: '.project'});});</script></body></html>